# Opervia Project Identity

## Product
- **Name:** Opervia (always use this exact casing)
- **Type:** B2B SaaS Rental + Workforce + Operations Platform
- **Positioning:** Opervia is the Operational OS for modern businesses.

## Taglines
- Primary: "Run Your Entire Operation From One Platform"
- Secondary: "Stop Managing Operations Through Spreadsheets & WhatsApp"

## Mission
Help businesses eliminate operational chaos by managing equipment rentals, staff, freelancers, scheduling, logistics, inventory, billing, analytics, notifications, and operational workflows.

## Brand Values
Simplicity, Operational clarity, Speed, Reliability, Automation, Scalability, Mobile-first experience, Professional enterprise UX

## Design Direction
Inspired by Linear, Stripe, Vercel, Notion. Use clean spacing, modern typography, minimal clutter, strong visual hierarchy, dashboard-first design.

## Naming Rules
- Use "Opervia" in all page titles, metadata, emails, auth flows, dashboards, legal pages, notifications, Stripe billing, onboarding, docs, PWA prompts, and SEO metadata.
- Never use alternate product names or generic placeholders like "MyApp" or "Platform".

## Copy Guidelines
- Focus on operational outcomes, not feature jargon.
- CTAs: "Start Free 5-Day Trial" (primary), "Book Demo" (secondary).
- Target audience: growing teams across Europe.
